  title="The CSS :has() Selector: the Parent Selector, Explained (2026)"
  description="The :has() relational pseudo-class lets you style an element based on what it contains or what follows it - the long-awaited parent selector. How it works, real examples, browser support, and the gotchas."
  cat="css"
  day={17}
  hero="/img/css-has-selector-hero.jpg"
